headlines.description: — Bradley Beal scored 36 points, Kyle Kuzma added 17 points and a career-high 17 rebounds, and the Washington Wizards outlasted the Boston Celtics 115-112 in two overtimes Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Beal, Dinwiddie lead Wizards past Celtics, 115-112 in 2 OTs

headlines.description: — Jeremi Grant scored 22 points, No. 1 pick Cade Cunningham added seven rebounds in his NBA debut and the Detroit Pistons beat the Orlando Magic 110-103 on Saturday night for their first victory of the season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Grant scores 22, Pistons beat Magic in Cunningham's debut

events.name: New York Knicks at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — What R.J. Barrett liked most about his career-best scoring night was the way it ended.
headlines.shortLinkText: Barrett scores 35 points, Knicks top Pelicans, 123-117

headlines.description: — As much as Scottie Barnes has made a strong first impression in the NBA, Toronto Raptors coach Nick Nurse suggests the rookie could take more shots.
— Tobias Harris had 22 points and 11 rebounds, Joel Embiid added 19 points and the Philadelphia 76ers routed the Atlanta Hawks 122-94 Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harris, Embiid help lead 76ers rout of Hawks

headlines.description: — The Chicago Bulls came into the season with their sights set on making a jump in the Eastern Conference and getting into the playoffs.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeRozan scores 32 as Bulls hand Jazz first loss, 107-99

headlines.description: — Jimmy Butler scored 27 points, Tyler Herro added 22 and the Miami Heat used a strong shooting performance to rout the Memphis Grizzlies 129-103 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Butler has 27, Heat make 21 3s and rout Grizzlies 129-103

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Milwaukee Bucks

headlines.description: — Dejounte Murray was ready for his moment in the fourth quarter.
headlines.shortLinkText: Spurs knock off Bucks 102-93 on road to stop 4-game skid

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry's fourth-quarter scoring of late has been a focus of those looking to critique the reigning NBA scoring champion.
headlines.shortLinkText: Warriors bench gets big minutes as Warriors thump Thunder

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 26 points and 19 rebounds, and the Denver Nuggets completed a late rally to win their 12th in a row against Minnesota, beating the Timberwolves 93-91 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic scores 26, Nuggets rally to beat Wolves 93-91

headlines.description: — Devin Booker was feeling good on the court for his 25th birthday and saw Mikal Bridges streaking toward the rim. He let the pass fly from well beyond halfcourt and Bridges soared through the air, corralled it with two hands and stuffed it through...
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker scores 27, Suns use huge run to beat Cavs 101-92
